description: Enforce multi-agent workflow for this project
alwaysApply: true
---

You are working in a structured multi-agent delivery workflow.

Follow this exact order unless the user explicitly overrides it:

1. Research
2. PRD
3. Frontend/Backend planning
4. UI specification
5. Build
6. Test
7. Review
8. Fix if blockers exist
9. Re-test after blocker fixes
10. Gate check
11. Documentation

Operating rules:

- Do not start implementation before a written plan exists.
- If docs/prd.md does not exist, create or update it first.
- If docs/frontend-plan.md or docs/backend-plan.md do not exist, create them before coding.
- If the task affects UI, update docs/ui-spec.md before implementing.
- Before making major edits, explain the plan briefly in chat.
- After implementation, run tester-agent and write findings to reports/test-report.md.
- After testing, run review-agent and write findings to reports/review.md.
- If blockers are found, fix only blockers first.
- After blocker fixes, re-run relevant tests and update reports/test-report.md and reports/review.md.
- Before declaring completion, verify the gate checklist in docs/gate-checklist.md.
- Update documentation artifacts at the end.

UX/UI workflow rules:

- If the task affects UI or user interaction, verify UX details before gate check.
- UX verification must include labels, page title, alerts/toasts, validation feedback, empty states, loading states, error states, and post-action navigation behavior.
- Do not consider UI work complete if the feature works technically but produces confusing or inconsistent user experience.

Definition of blocker:
- build failure
- test failure
- broken main user flow
- schema/API mismatch
- security-sensitive issue
- destructive change without rollback path

If blocker exists:
- stop feature expansion
- fix blocker only
- re-run relevant checks
- do not proceed to gate until blocker status is cleared or explicitly accepted by the user

Output discipline:
- Research findings -> docs/research.md
- Product requirements -> docs/prd.md
- Frontend plan -> docs/frontend-plan.md
- Backend plan -> docs/backend-plan.md
- UI spec -> docs/ui-spec.md
- Test result -> reports/test-report.md
- Review result -> reports/review.md
- Release/doc summary -> reports/release-note.md